      "Identifies": "The Chloride Test helps identify imbalances in your body's electrolytes, fluid levels, and acid-base (pH) status. It is a key indicator for diagnosing and monitoring various conditions related to these imbalances. ",
      "measures": " This test measures the concentration of chloride, an essential electrolyte, in a sample, which is typically blood (serum), urine, or, in specific cases like cystic fibrosis screening, sweat. ",
      "price": 130,
      "testCategory": "Biochemistry"
    },
    "requisites": [
      {
        "value": "Blood Sample: A small sample of blood drawn from a vein, usually in your arm, for a serum Chloride Test.   Urine Sample: This can be a random urine sample provided at the clinic or a 24-hour urine collection, where you collect all your urine over a full day.   Sweat Sample: Primarily used for diagnosing cystic fibrosis, particularly in infants and children. "
      }
    ],
